OL,10,GMicro-Electro-Mechanical Systems
OL,11,G(MEMS) are the tiny, unseen sensors
OL,12,Gthat connect our digital and physical
OL,13,Gworlds. They're in our phones, our
OL,14,Gcars, and even in the Tildagon badge
OL,15,Gyou're holding. But how do these
OL,16,Gmicroscopic marvels actually work? In
OL,17,Gthis talk, Harald Koenig of Bosch
OL,18,GSensortec will demystify MEMS
OL,19,Gtechnology. We’ll start with a
OL,20,Ghands-on example: the BMI270 Inertial
OL,22,D]CEMFFAX: The world at your fingertips\
